    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the top layer of a quilt, often left unfinished, without backing, filling, or quilting. Distinct from "summer spreads," which have finished edges and seams.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000099620/Legacy AAT data</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wordt gebruikt voor de bovenlaag van een gewatteerde deken, vaak onaf gelaten, zonder achterkantbekking, vulling of wattering  Anders dan  'zomer spreien' die afgewerkte randen en zomen hebben.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
